This paper discusses the use of external linguistic resources for information extraction, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions word sense disambiguation (WSD), which is a technique used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses how information extraction techniques can benefit from the application of WSD rules, which is a topic in neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
